    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1841" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βέλος</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βάλλω</span>):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">missile, shot;</span> anything thrown, whether a
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shaft</span> (arrow or dart), a stone, or the footstool
          hurled at Odysseus in <i><span class="en">Od. 17.464</span></i>; of
          the effects of a shot, <i><span class="en">Il. 8.513</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; βέλος ὀξύ</span>, sharp ‘pang,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 11.269</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἐκ βελέων</span>, out of
          ‘range.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
